ODE IX.

ΤΟ VALGIUS.

Nor always on the deiuged plain Doth Heaven, oh, Valgius! pour From humid clouds the oeoseless rain3

Nor storms perpetual vex the main, And losh tho sounding shore.

Nor do Armenia’s valleys sleep Beneath eternol frost 3

Nor unreposing whirlwinds sweep

The shivered oaks that crown the steep Of rude Gargonus’ coast.

Your grief, my friend, your fixed despair For Mystes’ loos deplored,

Cease not with Vespor’s rising star,

Nor when he fades before the oar Of light's returning lord.
